column7: British; in his early years based in London, the U.S. (Florida & Virginia), Leipzig & Paris; from 1897 Grez-sur-Loing (near Paris)-based
British; travelled extensively in Europe for many years
Bohemian; mainly Prague-based from 1857 (worked in the U.S. 1892-95)
Spanish; Cadiz, Madrid, Paris, Granada & finally Argentina-based
British; taught at the St. Paul's Girl School, Hammersmith, from 1905
Hungarian-French-German; had strong connections with Paris, Rome, Weimar, Budapest & Bayreuth
Austrian; successively based in Budapest (1888-91), Hamburg (1891-7), Vienna (1897-1907) & New York (1908-11)
Austrian; mainly Vienna-based, with significant stays in Salzburg, Milan, Paris, Munich & Prague
Russian; mainly St. Petersburg-based from c1849
Italian; from 1891 mainly Torre del Lago-based
Italian-Spanish; Naples-, Rome- & Venice-based to c1719; thereafter in Portugal & Spain
Austrian-American; mainly Vienna-based to 1933; U.S.-based thereafter, mainly in Los Angeles
German; in later years lived in Leipzig, Dresden & Dusseldorf
Finnish; from 1904 resided near Lake Tuusula
Russian; mainly St. Petersburg- & Moscow-based from 1850
